[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]37.1.
[normal] 
[normal]sharing
[normal] money fairly around England by taking financial distribution out of the hands of Ministers and replacing it with an agreement across English local government. The current arrangements for funding local government are opaque and subject to change with each
[normal] new national government. We need a fairer, more transparent and stable system for providing grant to local government based on needs and costs;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]37.2.
[normal] 
[normal]wider revenue raising powers including the ability to levy local tourist taxes
[normal],
[normal] reducing the dependence on cou
[normal]ncil tax and business rates and allowing areas the ability to reduce the tax burden on local taxpayers;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]37.3.
[normal] 
[normal]five year funding settlements across the public sector that provide more certainty and allow local partners to commit to joint investment and commissio
[normal]ning;
[normal] and
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]37.4.
[normal] 
[normal]the development of a market in municipal bonds that gives local government access to alternative forms of finance at more competitive rates than the Public Works Loans Board. The LGA is already undertaking feasibility work on this proposal.
